pokedex.name: Meltan
pokedex.description: They live as a group, but when the time comes, one strong Meltan will absorb all the others and evolve.

pokedex.name: Melmetal
pokedex.description: Centrifugal force is behind the punches of Melmetal’s heavy hex-nut arms. Melmetal is said to deliver the strongest punches of all Pokémon.

pokedex.name: Grookey
pokedex.description: It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.

pokedex.name: Thwackey
pokedex.description: When it’s drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won’t even notice that it’s already knocked out its opponent.

pokedex.name: Rillaboom
pokedex.description: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.

pokedex.name: Scorbunny
pokedex.description: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it’s raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.

pokedex.name: Raboot
pokedex.description: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.

pokedex.name: Cinderace
pokedex.description: It’s skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

pokedex.name: Sobble
pokedex.description: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.

pokedex.name: Drizzile
pokedex.description: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.

pokedex.name: Inteleon
pokedex.description: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes’ weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

pokedex.name: Skwovet
pokedex.description: It eats berries nonstop—a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It’ll show up on farms, searching for yet more berries.

pokedex.name: Greedent
pokedex.description: Common throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon has strong teeth and can chew through the toughest of berry shells.

pokedex.name: Rookidee
pokedex.description: Jumping nimbly about, this small-bodied Pokémon takes advantage of even the slightest opportunity to disorient larger opponents.

pokedex.name: Corvisquire
pokedex.description: The lessons of many harsh battles have taught it how to accurately judge an opponent’s strength.

pokedex.name: Corviknight
pokedex.description: With their great intellect and flying skills, these Pokémon very successfully act as the Galar region’s airborne taxi service.

pokedex.name: Blipbug
pokedex.description: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

pokedex.name: Dottler
pokedex.description: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

pokedex.name: Orbeetle
pokedex.description: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what’s around it—and what’s around it can include things over six miles away.

pokedex.name: Nickit
pokedex.description: Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.

pokedex.name: Thievul
pokedex.description: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.

pokedex.name: Gossifleur
pokedex.description: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.

pokedex.name: Eldegoss
pokedex.description: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.

pokedex.name: Wooloo
pokedex.description: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won’t be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.

pokedex.name: Dubwool
pokedex.description: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.

pokedex.name: Chewtle
pokedex.description: It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.

pokedex.name: Drednaw
pokedex.description: This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.

pokedex.name: Yamper
pokedex.description: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.

pokedex.name: Boltund
pokedex.description: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.

pokedex.name: Rolycoly
pokedex.description: It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.

pokedex.name: Carkol
pokedex.description: By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokedex.name: Coalossal
pokedex.description: While it’s engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

pokedex.name: Applin
pokedex.description: As soon as it’s born, it burrows into an apple. Not only does the apple serve as its food source, but the flavor of the fruit determines its evolution.

pokedex.name: Flapple
pokedex.description: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.

pokedex.name: Appletun
pokedex.description: Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.

pokedex.name: Silicobra
pokedex.description: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.

pokedex.name: Sandaconda
pokedex.description: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.

pokedex.name: Cramorant
pokedex.description: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.

pokedex.name: Arrokuda
pokedex.description: After it’s eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That’s when Cramorant swallows it up.

pokedex.name: Barraskewda
pokedex.description: It spins its tail fins to propel itself, surging forward at speeds of over 100 knots before ramming prey and spearing into them.

pokedex.name: Toxel
pokedex.description: It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak, but it can cause a tingling paralysis.

pokedex.name: Toxtricity
pokedex.description: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

pokedex.name: Sizzlipede
pokedex.description: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they’re well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.

pokedex.name: Centiskorch
pokedex.description: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.

pokedex.name: Clobbopus
pokedex.description: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn’t alarmed when that happens—it knows they’ll grow back. It’s about as smart as a three-year-old.

pokedex.name: Grapploct
pokedex.description: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.

pokedex.name: Sinistea
pokedex.description: The teacup in which this Pokémon makes its home is a famous piece of antique tableware. Many forgeries are in circulation.

pokedex.name: Polteageist
pokedex.description: Leaving leftover black tea unattended is asking for this Pokémon to come along and pour itself into it, turning the tea into a new Polteageist.

pokedex.name: Hatenna
pokedex.description: If this Pokémon senses a strong emotion, it will run away as fast as it can. It prefers areas without people.

pokedex.name: Hattrem
pokedex.description: Using the braids on its head, it pummels foes to get them to quiet down. One blow from those braids would knock out a professional boxer.

pokedex.name: Hatterene
pokedex.description: If you’re too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokémon is also known as the Forest Witch.

pokedex.name: Impidimp
pokedex.description: It sneaks into people’s homes, stealing things and feasting on the negative energy of the frustrated occupants.

pokedex.name: Morgrem
pokedex.description: With sly cunning, it tries to lure people into the woods. Some believe it to have the power to make crops grow.

pokedex.name: Grimmsnarl
pokedex.description: Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to opponents, ensnaring them as tentacles would.

pokedex.name: Obstagoon
pokedex.description: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.

pokedex.name: Perrserker
pokedex.description: After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.

pokedex.name: Cursola
pokedex.description: Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You’ll become stiff as stone if you touch it.

pokedex.name: Sirfetch’d
pokedex.description: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.

pokedex.name: Mr. Rime
pokedex.description: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.

pokedex.name: Runerigus
pokedex.description: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you’ll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.

pokedex.name: Milcery
pokedex.description: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.

pokedex.name: Alcremie
pokedex.description: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.

pokedex.name: Falinks
pokedex.description: The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.

pokedex.name: Pincurchin
pokedex.description: It stores electricity in each spine. Even if one gets broken off, it still continues to emit electricity for at least three hours.

pokedex.name: Snom
pokedex.description: It eats snow that piles up on the ground. The more snow it eats, the bigger and more impressive the spikes on its back grow.

pokedex.name: Frosmoth
pokedex.description: It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.

pokedex.name: Stonjourner
pokedex.description: Once a year, on a specific date and at a specific time, they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle.

pokedex.name: Eiscue
pokedex.description: This Pokémon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food, dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.

pokedex.name: Indeedee
pokedex.description: Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.

pokedex.name: Morpeko
pokedex.description: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they’re precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.

pokedex.name: Cufant
pokedex.description: If a job requires serious strength, this Pokémon will excel at it. Its copper body tarnishes in the rain, turning a vibrant green color.

pokedex.name: Copperajah
pokedex.description: These Pokémon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.

pokedex.name: Dracozolt
pokedex.description: The powerful muscles in its tail generate its electricity. Compared to its lower body, its upper half is entirely too small.

pokedex.name: Arctozolt
pokedex.description: This Pokémon lived on prehistoric seashores and was able to preserve food with the ice on its body. It went extinct because it moved so slowly.

pokedex.name: Dracovish
pokedex.description: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but this Pokémon can’t breathe unless it’s underwater.

pokedex.name: Arctovish
pokedex.description: The skin on its face is impervious to attack, but breathing difficulties made this Pokémon go extinct anyway.

pokedex.name: Duraludon
pokedex.description: The special metal that composes its body is very light, so this Pokémon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.

pokedex.name: Dreepy
pokedex.description: If this weak Pokémon is by itself, a mere child could defeat it. But if Dreepy has friends to help it train, it can evolve and become much stronger.

pokedex.name: Drakloak
pokedex.description: Without a Dreepy to place on its head and care for, it gets so uneasy it’ll try to substitute any Pokémon it finds for the missing Dreepy.

pokedex.name: Dragapult
pokedex.description: Apparently the Dreepy inside Dragapult’s horns eagerly look forward to being launched out at Mach speeds.

pokedex.name: Zacian
pokedex.description: This Pokémon has slumbered for many years. Some say it’s Zamazenta’s elder sister—others say the two Pokémon are rivals.

pokedex.name: Zamazenta
pokedex.description: This Pokémon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.

pokedex.name: Eternatus
pokedex.description: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokémon and the Dynamax phenomenon.

pokedex.name: Kubfu
pokedex.description: Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves. The moves it masters will determine which form it takes when it evolves.

pokedex.name: Urshifu
pokedex.description: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.

pokedex.name: Zarude
pokedex.description: Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It's incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokémon of the forest fear it.

pokedex.name: Calyrex
pokedex.description: No official data  revealed...

pokedex.name: Regieleki
pokedex.description: No official data  revealed...

pokedex.name: Regidrago
pokedex.description: No official data  revealed...
